This paper is about response generation for multi-turn conversations, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI) research. The paper proposes a new model for generating diversified and topic-coherent responses, which involves sequence-to-sequence net (Seq2Seq), latent Variable Hierarchical Recurrent Encoder-Decoder model (VHRED), and a dense topic matrix. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and speech processing. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which are all relevant to the topic of this paper.
